<p>The state of Vermont provides additional solar rebates through various programs administered by Green Mountain Power and other utilities. Solar rebates can reach up to \$8,500 for residential installations, with the exact amount depending on system size and utility territory. Vermont's Renewable Energy Standard creates additional value through Solar Renewable Energy Credits (SRECs), which solar system owners can sell to utilities to meet renewable energy requirements.</p>

